Police say the unidentified man's naked body was discovered earlier on Tuesday with severe injuries. JOHANNESBURG - The body of a man has been found bound to a street pole in Kagiso, west of Johannesburg. Police say the unidentified man's naked body was discovered earlier on Tuesday with severe injuries.A 25-year-old suspect has been taken in for questioning. The police's Solomon Sibiya says details remain sketchy but an investigation is underway. No one seems to know him, so we took him to the government mortuary. We even checked our books for missing persons but there was no trace of him there. 